Another suspect has been arrested in connection with the killing of police officers in Ngcobo in the Eastern Cape. The suspect’s arrest came days after 13 suspects appeared in the Ngcobo Magistrate’s Court in connection with the shooting. Last Wednesday, Warrant Officer Zuko Mbini, 45, Constable Zuko Ntsheku, 38, Nkosiphendule Pongco, 32, Sibongiseni Sondlana, 32 and Kuhle Metete, 27 were mowed down by a group of unknown men who entered the Ngcobo police station and randomly opened fire. Another victim who was hit and killed by a stray bullet near his home is a retired soldier Freddy Mpandeni, 58 who lived close to the police station. on Wednesday, the Ngcobo Methodist Church was at full capacity, as the families of the deceased paid their respect for the fallen heroes. The memorial service was honoured by different authorities, including members of the provincial legislature. Labour unions, members of the religious fraternity and media were also part of the divine service. -TNA Reporter